title: Google\Cloud\Talent\V4beta1\BatchUpdateJobsRequest
name: BatchUpdateJobsRequest
description:
Request to update a batch of jobs.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.BatchUpdateJobsRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The resource name of the tenant under which the job is created. The format is "projects/{project_id}/tenants/{tenant_id}", for example, "projects/api-test-project/tenant/foo". Tenant id is optional and the default tenant is used if unspecified, for example, "projects/api-test-project".

params.name: data.update_mask
params.description: Optional but strongly recommended to be provided for the best service experience, also increase latency when checking status of batch operation. If [update_mask][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.BatchUpdateJobsRequest.update_mask] is provided, only the specified fields in [Job][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job] are updated. Otherwise all the fields are updated. A field mask to restrict the fields that are updated. Only top level fields of [Job][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job] are supported. If [update_mask][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.BatchUpdateJobsRequest.update_mask] is provided, The [Job][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job] inside [JobResult][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.JobOperationResult.JobResult] will only contains fields that is updated, plus the Id of the Job. Otherwise, [Job][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job] will include all fields, which can yield a very large response.
